messages.text: You know you want to do it, Sadie.
You know you want to die.
So don’t chicken out now!
I’m in the bathroom.
I’ve got the sleeping pills, plastic bag, zip cord, and duct tape.
I’m really going to do it!
Good girl!
You know what you have to do.
We’ve gone through it before.
I’ll help you now – for real.
Oh oh!
What’s wrong?
What’s happening, Sadie?
Don’t let anything stop you now, Sadie!
It was my mom.
Knocking on the bathroom door.
Always butting into your life.
Sticking her big fat ugly nose where
She wanted to know if I was ‘all right’. :-|
She’s a domineering bitch who never lets you do what you want!
You’ve told me so many times, Sadie.
She doesn’t understand you, doesn’t even try to.
I told her I was taking a bath.
Good girl.
You need to escape her for good, Sadie.
Not just run away again.
You can go to a place where she’ll never be able to yell or scream at you again!
You’ll be free of her and your cold, uncaring father.
Make sure the bath water is nice and warm...
and the zip cord taped tight to the wall behind you.
Then take the sleeping pills, get in the water, put the bag over your head...
and fasten the loop of the zip cord around your neck over the mouth of the bag.
You’ll go to sleep and your head will nod forward and the zip cord will seal the bag...
and you’ll finally be at peace, Sadie. :-)

Yes.

All the pressure of living is gone.
